3.1.2 MDSD Tools
To apply AC-MDSD in practice we need a UML modeling tool and an MDSD generator. The UML tool must be able work with UML profiles for UML language extensions. At present, no mainstream UML tool exists that is able to evaluate modeling constraints, that is, able to check the assertions made on the metalevel in the form of OCL expressions3. Checking constraints therefore needs to be supported by the MDSD generator.
The generator tool must read the models provided by the respective UML tool and use them as input for generation. Today, most UML tools are able to save models in XMI format, but XMI quality varies. Thus the MDSD generator should offer predefined and customizable adapters for different modeling tools.
A more detailed discussion of tools and requirements can be found in Chapter 11.

