3.2.2 Transformations
After we have defined a UML profile, we can now tackle the actual code generation. This is not a simple task. Fortunately, some partial tasks are of a more general nature, and there are MDSD tools that will do the work for us. This includes the neutralization of the UML tool’s XMI output, template expansion control, input/output stream handling, and scanning and persistence of protected code regions for business logic implementation. Most MDSD generators are frameworks and use a template-like language to describe transformations from model to code in a straightforward way.

