A particularly useful feature of this template language is its support of polymorphism at the template level: at generator runtime, template definitions of the same name are bound via the dynamic type of the model element, similar to methods in Java. This is one of the most important OO concepts and serves to avoid ‘type switches’ (using instanceof) that are hard to maintain and often distributed all over the code.
